    "What this means is that HEC's supporters should reject a view of intentional action that has come to define the mainstream of work in action theory since Donald Davidson's Essays on Actions and Events (2001a [1980]) and embrace an alternative that has its roots in the earlier work of Elizabeth Anscombe (2000 Anscombe ([1954 Anscombe (], 1963 Anscombe (, 1983).",
